OL,5, The rise in mortgage rates means it is 
OL,6, now cheaper to rent a home than to buy 
OL,7, one for the first time since 2010,     
OL,8, according to Zoopla.                   
OL,10,FThe property website said the average  
OL,11,FUK rent is #1,163 per month, while     
OL,12,Faverage mortgage repayments are #1,285 
OL,13,Ffor first-time buyers on a 15% deposit.
OL,15,FZoopla said London and the South East  
OL,16,Fare the worst affected locations for   
OL,17,Fhigher mortgage costs versus rent.     
OL,19,FBut it is still cheaper to buy in areas
OL,20,Flike northern England and Scotland.    
